Last summer I went to the wrecking yard looking for some parts and came across 40-50 of these vans in the yard. Apparently the cash for clunkers took them off the streets and in the boneyard. These vehicles are built with a totally different mindset and that's totally cool.

name: DSTROYR DareDevil Hoodie
description:
The 2012 hoodie goes back to the original idea of designing hoodies. First hoodie in 2008 was the HeadHunters, then 2009 it was switched up as the GearHead Hunters.  Build upon the previous years design and flip it make the hoodies a evolution of an idea and almost tell a story with it.

So The DareDevil hoodie is a flip on last years Deeds Not Words hoodie. This time the Ghost Pilot is rocking a open face helmet with vintage aviator googles, horns and some broken chain links printed huge on the back.
DSTROYR Left chest hit is inspired by comics / cartoons.
Spark plugs on the left side of the hood printed in a charcoal grey. Right sleeve has the machete over bombs DSTROYR icon to finish it off.

name: Anything Goes
description:
Mixing it up a bit around here. Grew up on comic books thought I would add some of the more classical elements to this graphic. 
Typically the design is created 100% digitally with the computer. To go back to the OG comic style it was drawn on paper with a #2 pencil, inked with a Windsor Newton Series 7 brush, then scanned and finally digitally colored. This graphic has a more organic feel due to the drawing and inking process being done analog.
Enjoy!
Screen print graphic on 100% cotton t-shirt.
